-- Lexer error: `\u{8000000000000041}` = 2^63+65.  A DISTINCT bound from the two
-- range fixtures beside this one, and the reason a range check alone is not
-- enough: `parseRadix` accumulates in the compiler's own WRAPPING 63-bit Int, so
-- this used to wrap to 65 and reach `charFromCode` looking like a legitimate
-- 'A' — which is exactly what it silently printed (#567).  The lexer now rejects
-- >6 significant hex digits BEFORE parsing, so the wrap is unreachable.
-- Self-hosted reference: unicode escape '\u{8000000000000041}' is out of range...
x = "x\u{8000000000000041}y"
